d 'COBREAKCOINT': module to perform Quasi-Likelihood Ratio Tests for Cointegration, Cobreaking, and Cotrending
d
d     cobreakcoint implements quasi-likelihood ratio (QLR) tests
d for the joint analysis of cointegration,    cobreaking, and
d cotrending in a bivariate or multivariate system of I(1)
d variables that may contain	structural breaks in their
d deterministic components.    In applied macroeconomics and
d finance, researchers often test whether two non-stationary (I(1))
d variables    share a long-run equilibrium (cointegration). 
d However, many macroeconomic time series exhibit structural   
d breaks — permanent shifts in their means or trends caused by
d policy changes, economic crises, or	 institutional reforms.
d Standard cointegration tests (e.g., Engle-Granger, Johansen) can
d produce misleading	results when such breaks are present. 
d
d KW: cointegration
d KW: cobreaking
d KW: cotrending
d
d Requires: Stata version 14
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260419
d
d Author:   Merwan Roudane, NA
d Support: email  merwanroudane920@@gmail.com
d
f cobreakcoint.ado
f cobreakcoint.sthlp
f ../_/_cobreakcoint_display.ado
f ../_/_cobreakcoint_mata.ado
f ../_/_cobreakcoint_plot.ado
f cobreakcoint_example.do
f ../u/USbudget.dta
